          <div class="col-md-4">              
            <%= image_tag("lake-tahoe.jpg", alt: "Dr. Dan Shuman", class: "img-responsive") %>
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-8">
            <h2>Parking</h2>
            <p>There are several parking options for you when you come to the office. There is a parking garage for the SkyHouse South building which has over a hundred covered parking spots available. The entrance is just past the Ace Hardware as you are going south on Juniper. Just pull into the garage and stay right to take a ticket and head up the ramp. Bring your ticket with you so that we may validate your parking.</p>
            <p>You may choose to park on Juniper Street for free during certain hours of the day. There are also some spots on 6th Street. Please pay attention to all posted parking signs, especially on 6th because Park Atlanta monitors this area continually.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-4">
        <h3>What to Expect on Your First Visit</h3>
        <p>Dr. Shuman will typically spend your first visit going over your current complaint and getting a detailed history.  Then you will go through a comprehensive postural, orthopedic, neurological, chiropractic and functional movement assessment.  The results of your exam will be shared with you in the room and a strategy to help you achieve your health goals will be created.  If you just want to get out of pain, that’s fine.  If you want to resolve ingrained biomechanical imbalances and compensations, great! We will work with you and your goals to deliver the best service possible.  Treatment is usually started on the first visit so be sure to wear comfortable clothing (no jeans if possible).  We know that you’re busy so plan on an hour on your first visit.</p><br>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-md-12">
